@tqchen The current fusion algorithm cannot fuse concat with anything before it. For example, upsampling + concat, which is common in image segmentation networks, cannot be fused into a single op. The NNVM v1 algorithm can even fuse layout_transform + upsampling + concat into a single op, so I think this should be fixed.

In [this line](https://github.com/dmlc/tvm/blob/master/src/relay/pass/fuse_ops.cc#L236), ```field```'s parent should be not null, but the parent of tuple node (which is a concat node). The op pattern shouldn't simply be kOpaque, but kInjective in this case. But I don't know how to handle this for general cases.

The network before fusion:
```
def before(dshape):
    x = relay.var("x", shape=dshape)
    pooled = relay.nn.max_pool2d(x, pool_size=(2, 2), strides=(2, 2), padding=(0, 0))
    upsampled = relay.nn.upsampling(pooled, scale=2, layout="NCHW")
    concat = relay.concatenate((upsampled, x), axis=1)
    return relay.Function(relay.ir_pass.free_vars(concat), concat)
```
